headline: Stock Market Today: Nasdaq Drops As Nvidia Reverses Lower; Defense Stock Jumps (Live Coverage)
summary: Major stock indexes fell Thursday afternoon as investors weighed lower-than-expected weekly jobless claims and an earnings report from Nvidia released late Wednesday. Meanwhile, aerospace and defense play FTAI reversed higher with its outlook and dividend raised.

headline: Hot Spinoff Qnity Electronics Crushes Q4 Earnings Estimates
summary: Semiconductor equipment vendor Qnity Electronics smashed Wall Street's earnings target for the fourth quarter on higher-than-expected sales. Q stock rose on the news.

headline: Qnity Stock Rises After Earnings Beat. Why It Can Ride the AI Chips Wave in 2026.
summary: Thursday, Qnity reported fourth-quarter earnings per share of 82 cents from sales of $1.2 billion. Wall Street was looking for earnings per share of 63 cents from sales of $1.2 billion.

headline: Qnity forecasts upbeat full-year earnings as AI boom boosts demand
summary: Qnity Electronics forecast full-year 2026 earnings above analysts' estimates on Thursday, ‌as the newly listed semiconductor solutions provider ‌benefits from strong demand for artificial intelligence, high‑performance computing and ​next‑generation connectivity. The company's board of directors also authorized the repurchase of up to $500 million of outstanding common stock. Shares of the Wilmington, Delaware-based company rose ‌about 2% in ⁠premarket trading.
